It's hard to picture playing Hangman without the stick figure dangling in the wind but it's possible! Text your friend a series of underscores representing the number of letters in the word you've chosen. Your friend will respond with a letter they believe might be in the word. If the guess is correct, send your friend the underscores again, this time filling the correctly guessed letter. If they are wrong, you can reply with the number of guesses that remain (in a typical game of hangman, they're 6!).

The tradition of wearing a wedding ring on the fourth finger of the left hand can be traced back to ancient beliefs. This finger is often referred to as the “ring finger” because it was once thought to have a vein that leads directly to the heart. This romantic notion, called the “vena amoris” or the “vein of love,” has been a symbol of the connection and commitment between two people in a marriage. Even though we now know it’s not true, this tradition continues as a sweet way to show love. Unknown Businesses Of Punjab. Day 04 Of 28 Days, 28 States & Their Unknown Businesses. . . . . . Welcome to the vibrant state of Punjab, where tradition meets innovation. Join us on a journey through the diverse industries that make Punjab a powerhouse of economic growth and cultural richness. Punjab is the breadbasket of India, producing a whopping 16% of the nation's wheat and 10% of its rice. With 60% of its population working in agriculture, it's no wonder major FMCG giants like Pepsico, Coca-cola, ITC, Nestle, and Cargill have a significant presence here. If bicycles are your passion, Punjab is the place to be. It's home to 92% of India's bicycle parts production and 75% of the country's bicycles. Companies like Hero, Atlas, and Avon Cycles roll out top-quality bikes, with 80% of India's bicycle exports proudly bearing the Punjab mark. Punjab is the heartbeat of India's machinery and hand tool manufacturing industry, producing drill machines, electric saws, hammers, and more. Ludhiana and Jalandhar are the epicenters of this industry, contributing 20% of India's output. Punjab is a textile powerhouse, producing 65% of hosiery and a whopping 95% of woolen clothes in all of India. Its cotton yield per hectare is the highest in the nation, and with three huge textile parks, it caters to global fashion giants like GAP, Zara, and Puma. Punjab is a champion in the sports goods industry, accounting for 75% of India's production. From cricket gear to equipment for global events like the Tokyo Olympics and Commonwealth Games, Punjab's sports goods find their way onto the world stage. Amritsari navratri festival 😍🔔🙏 Brief History - The mela tradition, according to historical chronicles, started centuries ago with the belief that couples who pray at the temple for a male child would have their wish fulfilled. The couples thus blessed then bring their children dressed as langurs to the temple as a way of saying “thank you”. The Langoor dance, which the followers of the temple conduct to honor the powerful monkey God, is a common sight. Numerous worshippers arrive here each year dressed as Langoors. In Amritsar, the occasion is also referred to as Langoor Mela. 📍bada hanuman mandir Durgiana mandir Amritsar punjab india 🇮🇳

Follow @physicsloverz for more Margaret Heafield Hamilton was an American computer scientist, systems engineer, and business owner. She was Director of the Software Engineering Division of the MIT Instrumentation Laboratory, which developed on-board flight software for the Apollo space program. In 1986, she became the founder and CEO of Hamilton Technologies, Inc., in Cambridge, Massachusetts. The company was developed around the Universal Systems Language based on her paradigm of Development Before the Fact (DBTF) for systems and software design. Hamilton has published over 130 papers, proceedings, and reports about the 60 projects and six major programs in which she has been involved. On November 22, 2016, she was awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom by U.S. President Barack Obama for her work leading the development of on-board flight software for NASA’s Apollo Moon missions.
